[1] Cholera - Zambia (Lusaka)
Date: Mon 28 Mar 2016
Source: Zambia Daily Mail [edited]
https://www.daily-mail.co.zm/?p=63787


The number of cholera cases in Lusaka has risen to 412 and one person has died in George township since the disease broke out in February 2016, provincial medical officer Kennedy Malama has said. Dr Malama said as of [Sat 26 Mar 2016], at 18:00 hours, 17 new cholera cases were recorded with Kanyama cholera treatment centre recording 10 cases while Bauleni recorded 14.

He said one person of George Township was received dead on arrival at Matero referral cholera treatment centre. "We recorded a new death on [Sat 27 Mar 2016] where a patient was received and confirmed dead at Matero clinic, and tests later revealed that he died of cholera," he said.

Since the outbreak, Bauleni cholera treatment centre has attended to 261 cases, Kanyama 145, 5 have been recorded at Matero referral cholera treatment centre and one has been recorded in Chongwe.

[Byline: Catherine Mumba]

