[3] Cholera - Kenya (Wajir County)
Date: Mon 28 Mar 2016
Source: Citizen Digital [edited]
https://citizentv.co.ke/news/four-dead-18-hospitalised-following-cholera-outbreak-in-wajir-120095/


Following a cholera outbreak at Sarif area in Wajir County, 4 people have died while 18 others have been hospitalized. Confirming the incident, Wajir County Chief Health Officer Abdullahi Maalim Hassan said that despite the challenges that the county's health sector faces, everything is being done to control the situation.

Already the county health department has set aside emergency tents to cater to those affected, with more doctors and drugs being taken to the area to deal with the outbreak.

Since the 1st outbreak in Wajir in August 2015, 45 people have lost their lives out of the 2904 people who displayed cholera symptoms. The main cholera control centre in Wajir has just 6 patients left, indicating a reduction in the cases.

[Byline: Benjamin Wafula]

