[4] Cholera - Kenya (Nakuru County)
Date: Sun 27 Mar 2016
Source: The Star [edited]
http://www.the-star.co.ke/news/2016/03/27/19-new-cholera-cases-reported-in-naivasha_c1320536


As reported incidents of the health crisis continued to escalate, 19 new cholera cases have been confirmed in Naivasha town. The new cases have been reported in the sprawling Kihoto estate near Lake Naivasha. One of the latest victims had gone to visit the estate when he contacted the disease raising fears that he could have spread it.

A source from the public health ministry of Nakuru county termed the situation as critical warning that it could escalate to unmanageable levels. The officer who is not authorized to speak to the press said that the move to douse all shallow wells in the estate with chlorine was not helping. "The situation is worrying by the day as the number of those people affected continues to rise against limited resources," the officer said.

"Water consumed in this estate is not fit for animal consumption due to the high fecal matter but the residents are still drinking it," said the officer.

[Byline: Anthony Gitonga]

--
