[7] Cholera - Dominican Republic (Santiago Province)
Date: Fri 25 Mar 2016
Source: El Nuevo Diario [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
http://www.elnuevodiario.com.do/app/article.aspx?id=470641


The José María Cabral y Baez university regional hospital said that 4 of the 64 cases suspected cholera have been treated at the health center were positive. Ernesto Rodriguez, director of the medical center, said the affected people reside in the Jánico municipality, the municipal district of La Canela, and sectors Gurabo and Cienfuegos of the province [of Santiago]. Rodriguez added that no deaths have occurred.

At present, there are 7 patients with acute diarrhea admitted in the hospital.

